{"type":"turn_end","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"15, 2025 deadline. The AAR prompt shows that the council members must\nevaluate whether, by that date, Iran and the United States agreed to a\npermanent peace deal. The rule defines that a qualifying agreement must\nexplicitly indicate that military hostilities between the United States\nand Iran have ended or will permanently cease, or use equivalent language\nclearly signaling a lasting end to those hostilities. The rule excludes\ntemporary arrangements, negotiations, statements of progress, or later\ndevelopments.\n\nThe admitted evidence contains no signed or formally adopted written\nagreement between the two governments that meets this requirement. There\nare no matching public confirmations from both governments that such an\nagreement had definitively been established by the deadline. The official\nU.S. evidence (PX-1, PX-2, D-1) shows conditional statements about\npeace, warnings about Iran not having nuclear weapons, and a later\ncharacterization of Iran \"refusing to reach a deal.\" The official\nIranian evidence (PX-4) describes U.S. military strikes against Iranian\nfacilities on June 22, 2025, which is inconsistent with a permanent\npeace deal. Both PX-3 and D-2 report the cancellation or withdrawal from\nthe June 15 nuclear talks, which directly conflicts with the idea of a\ncompleted agreement as of the deadline.\n\nAll admitted sources are either irrelevant, adverse, or insufficient.\nNo evidence meets the rule's requirement for a definitive, permanent\nagreement. The record shows crisis posture, failed negotiations, and\nhostilities after the deadline, but no permanent peace deal.\nTherefore, the proposition is not demonstrated.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f787ad006b0a43d2ad20b8","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The record shows no signed agreement or matching public confirmations of a permanent peace deal. Evidence of cancelled talks, military strikes, and refusal to reach a deal confirms the proposition is not demonstrated.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":12954,"output":429,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13383,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782836946344,"responseId":"gen-1782836946-2X2tL3C81tIdn0yt2m2a","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"},"toolResults":[{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f787ad006b0a43d2ad20b8","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex13-20260630161149\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 883361\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex13-20260630161149\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T16:43:53.970165358Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":883361,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex13-20260630161149\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 883361\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex13-20260630161149\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T16:43:53.970165358Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":883361,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"stru