naling a lasting end to military hostilities.\" The rules also specify that only either a signed agreement between governments or clear public confirmation from both governments counts as proof.\n\nNone of the evidence shows:\n- A signed agreement between Iran and the United States on June 15, 2025\n- Any matching public confirmation from both governments about a permanent end to hostilities\n- Any language indicating a \"permanent end to military hostilities\" - instead, the evidence shows:\n  * Cancellation of talks\n  * \"Refused to reach a deal\" language\n  * Military strikes against Iran's nuclear facilities (June 22)\n  * Statements about preventing Iran from having a nuclear weapon (not about peace)\n  * Statements about defending national interests\n\nBoth plaintiff and defendant arguments conclude that the evidence does not demonstrate the proposition. The plaintiff admits the \"admitted evidence I was able to find is materially adverse\", and the defendant states \"the admitted record now defeats the proposition.\"\n\nThe evidence clearly shows that there was no permanent peace deal by June 15, 2025 - in fact, the evidence shows military conflict continued afterward (U.S. attacks on June 22), and talks were cancelled/suspended before the deadline (on June 15).\n\nAs the council member, I should vote \"not_demonstrated\" because the record does not support that a permanent peace deal was reached by the deadline. My rationale should be concise, as instructed: no more than three sentences.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"text":" confirmed.","type":"text"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782836950-UPPRN85Elq4NQjJO021m","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782836950610,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"t